&gt; thrust. They swung around and oriented on the shuttle, thier sensors
&gt; scanning over it for a moment, and then, as if noting the ship&#39;s
&gt; location and intent, the jets began to move off, banking over to
&gt; continue on their flight over and around the outside edge of the city.
&gt;
&gt; &gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; He looked out at the city.  Although he was a Predecon, he&#39;d never really
&gt; felt comfortable here.  The base felt like home, but in the city outside, he
&gt; was never sure from day-to-day whether he was going to be welcomed or
&gt; stabbed in the back.
&gt;
&gt; &lt;NEW&gt;
&gt;
&gt; The city looked almost dim with all the soot and debris that coated
&gt; it. Worker drones moved along its streets transporting natural ores
&gt; from one place to another. Much of the city was dark, littered with
&gt; dark allyways, dead end streets and dark pockets where neferious deals
&gt; of all sorts could take place.
&gt;
&gt; A few twin rotored helicoptors rose up over the city, thier watchful
&gt; beams straying over the darker alleys. The curious thing is that these
&gt; choppers, like the jets, registered as security and as Predacon, but
&gt; there was no Bushido IFF codes coming from them, they were definitly
&gt; something else. Also like the jets, the choppers paid little attention
&gt; to the incomming shuttle. Something interesting was happening in the
&gt; city, even the criminal element was becoming more unified, more
&gt; focused.
